 the standard one and it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is not able to capture substrings, so backreferences do not work."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Setting "},{"code":"startPosition","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" differs from just passing over a shortened"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"string and setting "},{"code":"notbol","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in the case of a pattern","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that begins with any kind of lookbehind assertion, such as “\\b”.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Unless ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"raw"},{"type":"text","text":" is specified in the options, "},{"code":"string","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" must be valid UTF-8."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfo","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" structure, used to get information on the match, is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stored in "},{"code":"matchInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if not "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Note that if "},{"code":"matchInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" then it is created even if the function returns ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"i.e. you must free it regardless if regular expression actually"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"matched.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"string"},{"type":"text","text":" is not copied and is used in "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Matc